<div class="notranslate transcript add-padding-right j-transcript">
<h3 class="transcript-header">
<i class="fa fa-file-o"></i>
Chef for Openstack
</h3>
<ol class="j-transcripts transcripts no-bullet no-style" itemprop="text">
<li>
1.
Chef for Openstack
Mohit Sethi
mohit@sethis.in
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-2-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Whoami?
Mohit Sethi
Developer, Technical Lead
Senior Engine..." target="_blank">
2.
</a>
Whoami?
Mohit Sethi
Developer, Technical Lead
Senior Engineer at HP R&amp;D
You?
• Developers?
• System Administrators?
• Architects?
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-3-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Journey so far?
• 2010-11:
• CFEngine,
• Puppet
• Chef
• 20..." target="_blank">
3.
</a>
Journey so far?
• 2010-11:
• CFEngine,
• Puppet
• Chef
• 2011 - Present
• Contributed to Chef, Knife cloud plugins such as ec2, azure, hp,
openstack, rackspace, google, cloudstack, vsphere, vcloud
• Written extensions for automation tools such as Vagrant, vagrant-
hp, vagrant-vsphere
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-4-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Goal for today
• Configuration Management Framework – Opsco..." target="_blank">
4.
</a>
Goal for today
• Configuration Management Framework – Opscode Chef,
• Principles,
• Automation Constructs
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-5-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="What is Chef?
Chef is a systems integration framework, buil..." target="_blank">
5.
</a>
What is Chef?
Chef is a systems integration framework, built to bring the
benefits of configuration management to you entire
infrastructure.
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-6-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Wait, What?
 " target="_blank">
6.
</a>
Wait, What?
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-7-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="What is Chef?
Chef is a tool that allows you to define the ..." target="_blank">
7.
</a>
What is Chef?
Chef is a tool that allows you to define the state your
servers(local or cloud) should be in and then enforces that
state on your servers.
An API for your entire Infrastructure.
A service that exposes data about the state of your
infrastructure
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-8-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Why should I use Chef?
You have Servers.
You need to config..." target="_blank">
8.
</a>
Why should I use Chef?
You have Servers.
You need to configure them.
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-9-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Why should I use Chef?
But I’ve my AWESOME bash scripts, wh..." target="_blank">
9.
</a>
Why should I use Chef?
But I’ve my AWESOME bash scripts, which already does most of
‘those’ things,
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-10-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Why else?
We are developers, we write multi-tier applicatio..." target="_blank">
10.
</a>
Why else?
We are developers, we write multi-tier applications
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-11-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Why else?
We like to make things interesting,
 " target="_blank">
11.
</a>
Why else?
We like to make things interesting,
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-12-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Why else?
Application grows,
 " target="_blank">
12.
</a>
Why else?
Application grows,
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-13-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Why else?
 " target="_blank">
13.
</a>
Why else?
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-14-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Why else?
Meanwhile 6 months later,
• How did I do that?
• ..." target="_blank">
14.
</a>
Why else?
Meanwhile 6 months later,
• How did I do that?
• Who changed that?
• Why did I do it what way?
• Then It dies,
• I have to rebuild it
• Did I forget anything
• How did I do it
• And you will be &gt;&gt;
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-15-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Why else?
And you will be…
 " target="_blank">
15.
</a>
Why else?
And you will be…
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-16-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Why Chef?
Provides:
 " target="_blank">
16.
</a>
Why Chef?
Provides:
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-17-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Architecture(1000’ view)
 " target="_blank">
17.
</a>
Architecture(1000’ view)
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-18-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Chef Client runs on your servers
 " target="_blank">
18.
</a>
Chef Client runs on your servers
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-19-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Client talks to a Chef Server
 " target="_blank">
19.
</a>
Client talks to a Chef Server
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-20-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Clients authenticate with RSA keys
 " target="_blank">
20.
</a>
Clients authenticate with RSA keys
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-21-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Knife is used to talk to Chef-Server &amp;
initiate convergence..." target="_blank">
21.
</a>
Knife is used to talk to Chef-Server &amp;
initiate convergence of a server.
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-22-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Principles
• Idempotent
• Provision Often
• Infrastructure ..." target="_blank">
22.
</a>
Principles
• Idempotent
• Provision Often
• Infrastructure As Code
• Data-Driven
• Thick Clients, Thin Server
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-23-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="#1 Idempotent
#1 Chef rule: Recipes/ Infrastructure code sh..." target="_blank">
23.
</a>
#1 Idempotent
#1 Chef rule: Recipes/ Infrastructure code should be
Idempotent.
The number of Chef runs should not affect the state of the
server. The server should converge on the first run. And unless
previously defined state changes, additional runs should not
change anything.
Say “what to do” not “how”
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-24-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="#2 Provision Often
If your recipes are not idempotent refer..." target="_blank">
24.
</a>
#2 Provision Often
If your recipes are not idempotent refer rule #1.
If they are, you should consider provisioning your servers often.
Possibly every 5 minutes. Seriously.
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-25-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="#3 Infrastructure As Code
Infrastructure should be represen..." target="_blank">
25.
</a>
#3 Infrastructure As Code
Infrastructure should be represented as code,
Server configuration, packages installed, relationships with
other servers, should be modeled with code to be automated.
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-26-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="#4 Data-Driven
• Separate of policy &amp; data (implemented usi..." target="_blank">
26.
</a>
#4 Data-Driven
• Separate of policy &amp; data (implemented using Attributes &amp;
DataBags)
• Infrastructure code should not have sensitive data. Though it
can have sane defaults.
• Sensitive data should be remain in a secured store, and
should only be shared with authorized clients.
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-27-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="#5 Thick Clients, Thin Servers
As much as possible much wor..." target="_blank">
27.
</a>
#5 Thick Clients, Thin Servers
As much as possible much work is done by Chef-Client(Nodes)
Pull not Push. Chef-client runs on each node &amp; will interact
with server when it needs to.
Server is designed to distribute data to each node, including
cookbooks, recipes, templates, files and so on.
Server also retains a copy of state of node at the conclusion of
every chef-client.
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-28-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Okay! let’s write some
infrastructure code…
 " target="_blank">
28.
</a>
Okay! let’s write some
infrastructure code…
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-29-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Vocabulary
• Nodes == Servers
• Attributes ≈ Variables
• Ro..." target="_blank">
29.
</a>
Vocabulary
• Nodes == Servers
• Attributes ≈ Variables
• Roles can define a Node’s attributes and what Recipes are applied to
that Node
• Clients == Anything that uses the API
• Resources are the basic building blocks to define state
• Related Resources are grouped into Recipes
• Related Recipes are grouped into Cookbooks
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-30-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Do I need to know Ruby?
A little
It’s a simple syntax
 " target="_blank">
30.
</a>
Do I need to know Ruby?
A little
It’s a simple syntax
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-31-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Chef-solo
Chef can also run stand-alone
 " target="_blank">
31.
</a>
Chef-solo
Chef can also run stand-alone
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-32-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Nodes == Servers
Nodes have Attributes
Attributes == Variab..." target="_blank">
32.
</a>
Nodes == Servers
Nodes have Attributes
Attributes == Variables
Attributes are Searchable
$ knife search node ‘platform:centos’
search(:node, ‘platform:centos’)
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-33-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Attributes
Attributes == Variables
Attributes are Searchabl..." target="_blank">
33.
</a>
Attributes
Attributes == Variables
Attributes are Searchable
$ knife search node ‘platform:centos’
search(:node, ‘platform:centos’)
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-34-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Nodes have RunList
A RunList defines:
What Roles or Recipes..." target="_blank">
34.
</a>
Nodes have RunList
A RunList defines:
What Roles or Recipes to apply in Order.
$ knife node show ks.ms.openstack.com –r
{
“run_list”: *
“role*os-base+”,
“role*os-identity+”,
]
}
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-35-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Nodes have Roles
Role: What describes a node
• webserver
• ..." target="_blank">
35.
</a>
Nodes have Roles
Role: What describes a node
• webserver
• dbserver
• glance-server
• keystone-server
• …etc
Roles have RunList
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-36-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Roles
• Roles have Run-List
 " target="_blank">
36.
</a>
Roles
• Roles have Run-List
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-37-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Roles
• Can have other roles!
 " target="_blank">
37.
</a>
Roles
• Can have other roles!
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-38-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Roles
• Can override default attributes
 " target="_blank">
38.
</a>
Roles
• Can override default attributes
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-39-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Roles
• Roles are Searchable
• To find all roles where attr..." target="_blank">
39.
</a>
Roles
• Roles are Searchable
• To find all roles where attribute: max_children takes value
50.
$ knife search role ‘max_children:50’
search(:role, ‘max_children:50’)
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-40-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Chef manages Resources on
Nodes
• Resource: Declare a descr..." target="_blank">
40.
</a>
Chef manages Resources on
Nodes
• Resource: Declare a description of the state a part of node should be
in.
• Have a type
• Have a name
• Have parameters
• Take action to put the resource
in the declared state
• Can send notification to other
resources.
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-41-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Providers
• Resource take action through providers.
• Know ..." target="_blank">
41.
</a>
Providers
• Resource take action through providers.
• Know how to actually perform the actions specified by a resource,
• Multiple providers per resources type
• Eg. Resource “package” have providers apt, yum, rubygems, portage,
macports, FreeBSD ports, etc
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-42-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Resources
Platform
Provider
 " target="_blank">
42.
</a>
Resources
Platform
Provider
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-43-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Recipes
• Recipes are list of Resources
• Apply resources i..." target="_blank">
43.
</a>
Recipes
• Recipes are list of Resources
• Apply resources in the order they are specified
• Recipes are `import` other recipes,
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-44-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Recipes are just Ruby!
 " target="_blank">
44.
</a>
Recipes are just Ruby!
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-45-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Cookbooks
• Cookbooks are packages for recipes,
• Distribut..." target="_blank">
45.
</a>
Cookbooks
• Cookbooks are packages for recipes,
• Distributable
• Versioned controlled.
• Can have dependency over other Cookbooks
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-46-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Cookbook Structure
• Attributes
• Assets(Files/Templates)
•..." target="_blank">
46.
</a>
Cookbook Structure
• Attributes
• Assets(Files/Templates)
• Providers
• Resources
• Recipes
• Metadata
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-47-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Cookbook Metadata
• Declares:
• Platform support
• Dependen..." target="_blank">
47.
</a>
Cookbook Metadata
• Declares:
• Platform support
• Dependencies
• Recipes
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-48-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="DataBags
• A data bag is a global variable that is stored a..." target="_blank">
48.
</a>
DataBags
• A data bag is a global variable that is stored as JSON data and is
accessible from a server.
• Create a data bag using knife
$ knife data bag create DATA_BAG_NAME (DATA_BAG_ITEM)
users = Chef::DataBag.new
• Can be encrypted
• Data values can be fetched from Recipes
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-49-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Community Cookbooks
• 1000+ cookbooks for everything
- data..." target="_blank">
49.
</a>
Community Cookbooks
• 1000+ cookbooks for everything
- databases, applications, CMS,
package management, Hadoop,
Cloud deployments
• http://community.opscode.com
• https://launchpad.net/openstack-chef
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-50-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Platform Support
• Debian
• Ubuntu
• RHEL
• Centos
• OS X
•..." target="_blank">
50.
</a>
Platform Support
• Debian
• Ubuntu
• RHEL
• Centos
• OS X
• Windows
• FreeBSD
• SUSE Enterprise
• Solaris
• SUSE
• IBM AIX
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-51-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Chef Flavors
• Opscode Hosted-Chef
• http://manage.opscode...." target="_blank">
51.
</a>
Chef Flavors
• Opscode Hosted-Chef
• http://manage.opscode.com
• Hosted SaaS version of Chef.
• Opscode Enterprise/Private Chef
• Private deployments of Opscode Chef Server
• On-Premise deployments
• Open Source Chef
• Installation
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-52-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Cloud support
• Cloud support by Knife
• EC2, Rackspace, HP..." target="_blank">
52.
</a>
Cloud support
• Cloud support by Knife
• EC2, Rackspace, HP, Google, Azure, CloudStack, OpenStack, vSphere, vCloud, Joyent, etc
• Extensible
• Implement own Resources &amp; Providers,
</li>
<li>
<a href="http://image.slidesharecdn.com/chefforopenstack-130824074550-phpapp01/95/chef-for-openstack-53-638.jpg?cb=1379753463" title="Questions??
self.intro do |mohit|
mohit.twitter = @mohitset..." target="_blank">
53.
</a>
Questions??
self.intro do |mohit|
mohit.twitter = @mohitsethi,
mohit.email = mohit@sethis.in
end
</li>
</ol>
</div>
